items.subhead: Vegas one win from Stanley Cup Final; Winnipeg seeks elusive first goal
items.seoTitle: Vegas Golden Knights Winnipeg Jets game 5 preview
items.seoDescription: The Vegas Golden Knights will try to become the third NHL team to reach the Stanley Cup Final in its inaugural season when they play the Winnipeg Jets in Game 5 of the Western Conference Final at Bell MTS Place on Sunday.

items.preview:
GOLDEN KNIGHTS at JETS

3 p.m. ET; NBC, CBC, TVAS, SN

Vegas leads best-of-7 series 3-1

WINNIPEG -- The Vegas Golden Knights will try to become the third NHL team to reach the Stanley Cup Final in its inaugural season when they play the Winnipeg Jets in Game 5 of the Western Conference Final at Bell MTS Place on Sunday.

items.headline: Golden Knights advance to Stanley Cup Final, eliminate Jets in Game 5
items.subhead: Fleury makes 31 saves, Reaves scores tiebreaking goal for Vegas
items.seoTitle: Vegas Golden Knights Winnipeg Jets Game 5 Recap
items.seoDescription: The Vegas Golden Knights advanced to the Stanley Cup Final with a 2-1 win against the Winnipeg Jets in Game 5 of the Western Conference Final at Bell MTS Place on Sunday.Vegas will face the winner of the Tampa Bay Lightning and Washington Capitals. The Lightning lead that best-of-7 series 3-2.

items.preview:
WINNIPEG -- The Vegas Golden Knights advanced to the Stanley Cup Final with a 2-1 win against the Winnipeg Jets in Game 5 of the Western Conference Final at Bell MTS Place on Sunday.

Vegas will play the winner of the Tampa Bay Lightning and Washington Capitals. The Lightning lead that best-of-7 Eastern Conference series 3-2.
